    ## Action Space
    Box(-1.0, 1.0, (28,), float32) — absolute joint positions for arm (4) + hand (24).

    ## Observation Space
    Box(-inf, inf, (39,), float64)

    | Num    | Key in env_state      | Description                                              |
    |--------|-----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
    | 0-26   | hand_qpos (27,)       | Joint angles: arm (indices 0-3) + hand (indices 4-26)    |
    | 27     | latch_pos             | Angular position of the door latch (rad)                 |
    | 28     | door_hinge / door_pos | Door hinge angle (rad); task complete when >= 1.35 rad   |
    | 29-31  | palm_pos (3,)         | Palm center position (x, y, z) in world frame            |
    | 32-34  | handle_pos (3,)       | Door handle position (x, y, z) in world frame            |
    | 35-37  | palm_handle_delta (3,)| palm_pos - handle_pos (signed distance vector)           |
    | 38     | door_open             | +1.0 if door_hinge > 1.0 rad, else -1.0                  |

    Additional env_state keys:
    - joint_velocities (30,): joint velocity vector
    - joint_forces (28,): actuator force vector

    ## Task
    Maximize door opening: undo the latch, then swing the door open as far as possible.
    The door hinge angle ranges from 0 (closed) to ~1.57 rad (fully open).
    The task is considered solved when door_hinge >= 1.35 rad.

    ## Reward Function Signature
    def compute_reward(door_hinge, palm_pos, handle_pos, palm_handle_delta, latch_pos, door_open, ...):
        # Use named arguments matching env_state keys above
        ...
        return total_reward, {"component_name": component_value, ...}

    ## Example Reward Components
    - get_to_handle: reward for moving palm close to door handle
    - open_door: reward for increasing door_hinge angle
    - latch_reward: reward for reducing latch_pos (unlatching)
    - door_open_bonus: sparse bonus when door_hinge exceeds threshold
